{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-02-05",
 "title": "A Drunk Ensign and the Wookiee",
 "summary": "On the Ship Services deck of the NRSC Deliverance, a half-asleep, possibly drunk Ensign named Wes carelessly greets the towering Wookiee officer Geroam as \"man,\" provoking the Wookiee's fury over the disrespect to a senior officer. As Ghost Squadron lieutenant Bazil McKenzie arrives from the lift with his fellow pilot Jenkins, Geroam seizes Wes by the collar and hauls him off toward the brig while commander Altair Quila trails along, baffled by the roaring exchange. Bazil, arriving too late to intervene, greets Altair and warily clocks the proud, authoritative arrival of John Donivan stepping from another lift. The scene closes with Geroam manhandling the resisting Ensign toward the turbolift and the brig.",
